# Game Architecture

## Module Structure

- `project.godot` — Godot 4 project file. Prefer editor-driven changes for `.godot`, `.tscn`, `.tres`.
- `src/core/` — runtime orchestration and app entrypoints (`main`, `client`, `server`).
- `src/net/` — networking transport/protocol (`network_client`, `network_server`).
- `src/entities/` — gameplay entities (tanks, shells, specs, shared assets).
- `src/controllers/` — player and AI controller scenes/scripts.
- `src/levels/` — playable level scenes and logic.
- `src/ui/` — UI scenes, widgets, overlays, HUD.
- `src/global_assets/` — shared art, audio, UI resources.
- `src/game_data/` — data resources and config assets.
- `src/config/`, `src/autoloads/` — config and autoload scripts.
- `src/api/` — HTTP API clients (see game-code-patterns rule for conventions).

## Runtime Architecture

- `src/core/main.gd` selects runtime mode (client vs dedicated server).
- `src/core/client.gd` owns client game flow, composes `$NetworkClient`.
- `src/core/server.gd` owns server tick/runtime loop, composes `$NetworkServer`.
- Keep transport/protocol code in `src/net/`; don't mix server transport into client scripts.
- `just game::fix` — editor cache refresh, build, format, lint.

## Scene Lifecycle Philosophy

Scene tree as truth: nodes that should always be present are added as part of the scene and referenced by unique names. They are always available to parents.

Instead of calling activation methods on children, let them handle internal logic in `_ready()` and trigger activation via `add_child()`.

### Lifecycle Principles

- Scene composition encodes invariants; node lifetime encodes state.
- Scene-wired dependencies are always present — no runtime null checks for invariant structure.
- Ephemeral gameplay/session state = dynamic child nodes added/removed on lifecycle transitions.
- Prefer mount/unmount of subtree roots over distributed `is_active` flags.
- Lifecycle boundaries explicit: orchestrator nodes own creation/teardown and expose stable signals to parents.

## UI Resource Reactivity

For UI reflecting `Resource` state: bind once in `_ready()` to the shared `Resource` instance, hydrate initial values immediately, update via the resource's change signals.

- Avoid cross-tree parent-driven `display_*` fanout refresh calls.
- Keep signal handling local to the UI node that owns the visual element.

## Folder Structure

- Mirror ownership and lifecycle boundaries in the scene tree.
- Stable orchestrators at domain root (e.g. `arena/arena_client.*`).
- Dynamic session/match subtrees under nested folders (e.g. `arena/runtime/*`).
- Perfect 1:1 tree mirroring not required, but parent orchestrator + dynamic subtree grouping stays consistent.

## Refactor Rules

- Prioritize reducing architectural complexity and clarifying ownership over minimizing diff size.
- No new util/helper files unless explicitly requested.
- Prefer deleting/merging redundant files and call paths.
- Breaking internal APIs allowed during refactors — migrate all call sites in the same change.
- Choose the largest safe refactor validatable in one pass, not the smallest local patch.
- A refactor is incomplete if ownership is still split across layers after behavior is fixed.
